Source: hdfs-fdw
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), g++, default-jdk-headless, libxml2-dev
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/EnterpriseDB/hdfs_fdw

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-hdfs-fdw
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-hdfs-fdw
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, default-jre-headless, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Hadoop/Hive foreign data wrapper for PostgreSQL PGVERSION
 hdfs_fdw accesses Hive-compatible remote data sources through an embedded JVM
 and JDBC bridge. A suitable Hive JDBC driver and remote service are required
 for actual queries.
